The dihedral group as a group of automorphisms - ScienceDirect

















Skip to main content


ScienceDirectJournalsBooksRegisterSign inHelpJournalsBooksRegisterSign inHelp

 Download full text in PDFDownloadExport Advanced JavaScript is disabled on your browser. Please enable JavaScript to use all the features on this page.Journal of AlgebraVolume 375, 1 February 2013, Pages 1-12The dihedral group as a group of automorphismsDedicated to Professor V.D. Mazurov on the occasion of his 70th birthday. Author links open the author workspace.PavelShumyatskyOpens the author workspaceDepartment of Mathematics, University of Brasilia, Brasilia-DF, 70910-900, BrazilShow morehttps://doi.org/10.1016/j.jalgebra.2012.04.035Get rights and contentUnder an Elsevier user licenseopen archiveAbstractSuppose that D=〈α,β〉 is a dihedral group generated by two involutions α and β. Let D act on a finite group G in such a manner that CG(αβ)=1. We show that if CG(α) and CG(β) are both nilpotent of class c, then G is nilpotent and the class of G is bounded solely in terms of c. If both CG(α) and CG(β) are of exponent dividing e, then the exponent of G is bounded solely in terms of e and |D|. Previously, results of this kind were known only for groups acted on by Frobenius groups of automorphisms.MSC20D45KeywordsAutomorphismsCentralizersAssociated Lie ringsFinite groupsRecommended articlesCiting articles (0)Copyright © 2012 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.Recommended articlesCiting articles

















