s2
s1
s0
r2
r1
r0


For example, s2s1 = r1, because the reflection s1 followed by the reflection s2 results in a rotation of 120°. The order of elements denoting the composition is right to left, reflecting the convention that the element acts on the expression to its right. The composition operation is not commutative.
In general, the group Dn has elements r0, …, rn−1 and s0, …, sn−1, with composition given by the following formulae:







