n


{\displaystyle n}

 reflection symmetries. Usually, we take 



n


{\displaystyle n}

≥3 here.The associated rotations and reflections make up the dihedral group 




D

n




{\displaystyle D_{n}}

 . If 



n


{\displaystyle n}

 is odd, each axis of symmetry connects the midpoint of one side to the opposite vertex. If 



n


{\displaystyle n}

